	<message key="plugins.generic.pkpdc.name">PKP Dublin Core Extender</message>
	<message key="plugins.generic.pkpdc.description">This plugin extends the Dublin Core schema with additional fields when used in conjunction with the Public Knowledge Project's Open Journal Systems.</message>
	<message key="plugins.generic.pkpdc.archive.form.pkpDcHandling">OJS DC Extensions</message>
	<message key="plugins.generic.pkpdc.archive.form.pkpDcHandling.description"><![CDATA[Open Journal Systems (<a href="http://pkp.sfu.ca/ojs">http://pkp.sfu.ca/ojs</a>) maintains metadata in a more granular form than Dublin Core. When fetching Dublin Core data via an OAI harvest, you may choose to unpack OJS data into its more granular field set by choosing the version of Open Journal Systems you are using in the above field.]]></message>
